# 16_text_popover_finish — substrate-layer suite for the Text
# placement popover's remaining widgets (s196 m3).
#
# Substrate-style test (per TESTING.md grandfather clause). Each
# sub-test proves the substrate contract holds — abbrev resolves,
# verbs dispatch, queries read back.
#
# Scope (s196 m3): the standalone widgets in the Text popover not
# already covered by test 14 — Place button, Bold / Italic
# CheckButtons, family DropDown, anchor DropDown. The X / Y / Size
# SpinButtons were migrated in s196 m1 as a helper-pulled-forward
# side effect; they're already covered by test 14.
#
# Architectural note: text_bold_btn and text_italic_btn were
# value-held Gtk::CheckButton members in the original design.
# The substrate's CheckButton constructor takes the abbrev as its
# first argument, which has to happen at build_text_popover() time
# (not at Impl default-construction). m3 flipped both members to
# pointer-held curvz::widgets::CheckButton, allocated inside
# build_text_popover(). All call sites that read .get_active() /
# .set_active() updated to pointer syntax with null guards.
#
# DSL note (carried from m1): the DSL lexer is kind-strict. Bool
# literals (true / false) are unambiguous; no analogue of the
# Int/Double trap.
#
# The tested abbrevs:
#
#   Text popover  pop_tb_txt_pl   (Place Button)
#                 pop_tb_txt_b    (Bold CheckButton)
#                 pop_tb_txt_i    (Italic CheckButton)
#                 pop_tb_txt_fam  (Font family DropDown — system-dependent contents)
#                 pop_tb_txt_an   (Anchor DropDown — fixed {Left, Centre, Right, Justify})
#
# Test protocol:
#   1. Open the Scripter window.
#   2. Load this script.
#   3. Run. Every line should PASS.
#
# Side effects: the Bold / Italic CheckButtons are toggled during
# the run and explicitly restored to false (their launch default
# per the build-time pattern). The anchor DropDown is moved
# through its options and restored to 0 (Left, the launch default
# per the popup-open callback). The family DropDown's selected
# index is not changed by this test (the system font list is
# environment-dependent and there's no portable way to assert on a
# specific font name).

#[sub] Text popover — Place button label.

assert pop_tb_txt_pl label == "Place"

#[sub] Text popover — Bold CheckButton round-trip.

pop_tb_txt_b set true
assert pop_tb_txt_b active == true
pop_tb_txt_b set false
assert pop_tb_txt_b active == false

#[sub] Text popover — Italic CheckButton round-trip.

pop_tb_txt_i set true
assert pop_tb_txt_i active == true
pop_tb_txt_i set false
assert pop_tb_txt_i active == false

#[sub] Text popover — Family DropDown is populated.

# System font list — can't assert specific names portably, only
# that the DropDown has at least one entry.
get pop_tb_txt_fam count

#[sub] Text popover — Anchor DropDown — Left wins by default.

assert pop_tb_txt_an selected == 0
assert pop_tb_txt_an text == "Left"

#[sub] Text popover — Anchor DropDown — set Centre (index 1).

pop_tb_txt_an set 1
assert pop_tb_txt_an selected == 1
assert pop_tb_txt_an text == "Centre"

#[sub] Text popover — Anchor DropDown — set Right (index 2).

pop_tb_txt_an set 2
assert pop_tb_txt_an selected == 2
assert pop_tb_txt_an text == "Right"

#[sub] Text popover — Anchor DropDown — set Justify (index 3).

pop_tb_txt_an set 3
assert pop_tb_txt_an selected == 3
assert pop_tb_txt_an text == "Justify"

#[sub] Text popover — Anchor DropDown — pick "Left" by name, restores baseline.

pop_tb_txt_an pick "Left"
assert pop_tb_txt_an selected == 0
assert pop_tb_txt_an text == "Left"

#[sub] Done. 5 new substrate widgets, all addressable.
